# Styling

## CSS Modules (Recommended)

```typescript
import styles from './MyComponent.module.css'

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div className={styles.container}>
      <p className={styles.text}>Hello</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Dynamic Theming with useTheme()

```typescript
import { useTheme } from '@/theme/context'

function MyComponent() {
  const { colors, isDarkMode } = useTheme()

  return (
    <div style={{ backgroundColor: colors.background }}>
      <p style={{ color: colors.text }}>Hello</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## CSS Custom Properties

Define theme values as CSS variables in `:root`:
```css
:root {
  --background: #f8f9fa;
  --text: #1a1a1a;
  --primary: #4A90E2;
}

@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --background: #0a0a0a;
    --text: #ffffff;
  }
}
```

## Critical Rules

- **Never** use hard-coded colors (hex codes) in components - use CSS variables or theme
- **Never** use hard-coded font sizes - use design system tokens
- Use CSS Modules for component-specific styles
- Use global CSS for base styles and CSS custom properties

## Responsive Design

- Use CSS media queries for responsive layouts
- Mobile-first approach: start with mobile styles, add breakpoints for larger screens
- Common breakpoints: 480px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1024px (desktop)

## Class Naming (CSS Modules)

- Use camelCase: `container`, `headerTitle`, `buttonPrimary`
- Keep names descriptive and component-scoped
